body:
The current TVM runtime doesn't scale up well on multi-core CPUs. This PR fixes this issue by

1. adding thread affinity to minimize the contention (Only introduced Linux version, TBD for MacOS and Windows);
2. using a lock-free single-producer-single-comsumer bounded queue to replace the existing `ParallelTaskQueue` to largely get rid of the use of mutex and condition variable;
3. making the default busy waiting time of a worker to be longer, so that it won't frequently go to sleep between parallel regions.

The new threadpool runs 2x faster than the current one, and outperforms OpenMP on Intel Skylake by 5-10%.

Example usage:

```js
var tvm = tvm_runtime.create(Module);
var syslib = tvm.systemLib();

var graph_json_str = "...";
var ctx = tvm.context("opengl", 0);
var loaded_module = tvm.createGraphRuntime(graph_json_str, syslib, ctx);

var x = tvm.empty(4, "float32", ctx).copyFrom([1, 2, 3, 4]);
loaded_module.set_input("x", x);

base64_params = "...";
loaded_module.load_base64_params(base64_params);

loaded_module.run();

var z = tvm.empty(4, "float32", ctx);
loaded_module.get_output(0, z);
```

enable B and C reuse A1 buffer, before this patch, B(200 int16) took all space of A1(200 float32) 
```
with ib.for_range(0, 10, name="j") as j:
            A = ib.allocate("float32", 200, name="A", scope="local.L0A")
            A1 = ib.allocate("float32", 200, name="A1", scope="local.L0A")
            A[j] = 1.2
            A1[j] = 1.3
            B = ib.allocate("int16", 200, name="B", scope="local.L0A")
            B[j] = tvm.const(1, "int16")
            C = ib.allocate("int16", 200, name="C", scope="local.L0A")
            C[j] = tvm.const(1, "int16")
            D = ib.allocate("int16", 200, name="D", scope="local.L0A")
            D[j] = B[j] + C[j]
            E = ib.allocate("int16", 400, name="E", scope="local.L0A")
            E[j] = tvm.const(1, "int16")
            A2 = ib.allocate("float32", 200, name="A2", scope="local.L0A")
            A2[j] = A[j]
```
also add a case for 
```
// then start looking at smaller buffers.
      for (auto it = mid; it != begin;) {
        --it;
        StorageEntry *e = it->second;
        if (e->attach_scope_ != attach_scope) continue;
        if (e->scope != scope) continue;
        if (e->elem_type != op->type.element_of()) continue;
        const_free_map_.erase(it);
        return e;
      }
```

#883 introduced changes that that are only applicable to resnet18 and mobilenet workloads. For other workloads, it aborts with exception.

This PR allows non resnet18 or mobilenet workload to use a fall back schedule.

